   // Lot acquisition date\n);\n```\n\n### Algorithm - Step-by-Step:\n\n**Step 1: Extract existing annotation (lines 241-243)**\n```cpp\nannotation_t* current_annotation = nullptr;\nif (commodity.annotated)\n  current_annotation = &as_annotated_commodity(commodity).details;\n```\nIf the amount's commodity is already annotated (from a previous purchase), save its annotation details.\n\n**Step 2: Compute per-unit cost (line 245)**\n```cpp\namount_t per_unit_cost = (is_per_unit || amount.is_zero()) \n  ? cost.abs() \n  : (cost / amount).abs();\n```\n- If cost is marked as per-unit (@), use it directly\n- If cost is total (@@), divide by amount to get per-unit\n- Handle zero amounts safely\n\n**Step 3: Normalize per-unit cost precision (lines 256-257)**\n```cpp\nif (per_unit_cost.has_commodity() && per_unit_cost.keep_precision())\n  per_unit_cost.in_place_roundto(\n    static_cast<int>(per_unit_cost.display_precision())\n  );\n```\n**Critical for issue #1032:** Round per-unit cost to its display precision so that lot prices computed from total costs (@@) can be matched against the displayed value when users reference them explicitly.\n\n**Step 4: Conditionally add to price history (lines 264-269)**\n```cpp\nif (add_price && !per_unit_cost.is_realzero() &&\n    (current_annotation == nullptr ||\n     !(current_annotation->price && current_annotation->has_flags(ANNOTATION_PRICE_FIXATED))) &&\n    commodity.referent() != per_unit_cost.commodity().referent()) {\n  exchange(commodity, per_unit_cost, moment ? *moment : CURRENT_TIME());\n}\n```\nOnly record price if:\n- `add_price` flag is true\n- Price is non-zero\n- Commodity doesn't have a fixated price (user-specified with `{=price}`)\n- Currencies are different\n\n**Step 5: Calculate final_cost (line 272)**\n```cpp\nbreakdown.final_cost = !is_per_unit ? cost : cost * amount.abs();\n```\n- If cost was specified as total, use it directly\n- If cost was per-unit, multiply by amount quantity\n\n**Step 6: Calculate basis_cost (lines 276-279)**\n```cpp\nif (current_annotation && current_annotation->price)\n  breakdown.basis_cost = (*current_annotation->price * amount).unrounded();\nelse\n  breakdown.basis_cost = breakdown.final_cost;\n```\n**Critical for gain/loss:** \n- If selling an existing annotated lot, use the original purchase price × amount = original cost basis\n- Otherwise, use the transaction's stated cost as the basis (no gain/loss when buying)\n\n**Step 7-11: Create annotated amount (lines 283-301)**\n```cpp\nannotation_t annotation(\n  per_unit_cost,\n  lot_date ? lot_date \n           : (moment ? std::optional<date_t>(moment->date()) \n                     : std::optional<date_t>{}),\n  tag\n);\n\nannotation.add_flags(ANNOTATION_PRICE_CALCULATED);\nif (current_annotation && current_annotation->has_flags(ANNOTATION_PRICE_FIXATED))\n  annotation.add_flags(ANNOTATION_PRICE_FIXATED);\nif (!lot_date && moment)\n  annotation.add_flags(ANNOTATION_DATE_CALCULATED);\nif (tag)\n  annotation.add_flags(ANNOTATION_TAG_CALCULATED);\n\nbreakdown.amount = amount_t(amount, annotation);\n```\nCreate new annotation with:\n- `per_unit_cost` as the price\n- Lot date (explicit or calculated from transaction date)\n- User tag if provided\n- Flags marking which fields were calculated vs. user-specified\n\n---\n\n## 3. annotation_t Structure\n\n**File:** `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-164/src/annotate.h:52-99`\n\n```cpp\nstruct annotation_t : public flags::supports_flags<>, \n                      public equality_comparable<annotation_t> {\n  std::optional<amount_t> price;      // Per-unit cost price\n  std::optional<date_t> date;          // Acquisition/lot date\n  std::optional<string> tag;           // User-supplied tag\n  std::optional<expr_t> value_expr;    // Value expression (rare)\n  // flags inherited\n};\n```\n\n### Key Flags:\n```cpp\n#define ANNOTATION_PRICE_CALCULATED 0x01   // Price was auto-calculated\n#define ANNOTATION_PRICE_FIXATED 0x02      // Price fixed: {=price}\n#define ANNOTAT