ties_map:\n\n**File:** `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-164/src/pool.h:68-72`\n\n```cpp\nusing annotated_commodities_map =\n    std::map<std::pair<string, annotation_t>, \n             std::shared_ptr<annotated_commodity_t>>;\n\nannotated_commodities_map annotated_commodities;\n```\n\n**Key:** `std::pair<base_symbol, annotation_t>`\n- **base_symbol:** e.g., \"BTC\"\n- **annotation_t:** price, date, tag that uniquely identifies the lot\n\n**Lookup:** The map's key includes the full `annotation_t`, so lots are distinguished by all their details. Two lots with same price but different dates = different keys.\n\n**Efficiency:** Logarithmic `O(log n)` lookup by base symbol + annotation. To find all lots of a commodity, you must iterate the entire map (no reverse index).\n\n---\n\n## 5. How Annotated Commodities Get Attached to Amounts\n\n**File:** `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-164/src/amount.cc:950-975`\n\n```cpp\nvoid amount_t::annotate(const annotation_t& details) {\n  commodity_t* this_base;\n  annotated_commodity_t* this_ann = nullptr;\n\n  // Get the base commodity\n  if (commodity().has_annotation()) {\n    this_ann = &as_annotated_commodity(commodity());\n    this_base = &this_ann->referent();\n  } else {\n    this_base = &commodity();\n  }\n\n  // Find or create annotated commodity in pool\n  if (commodity_t* ann_comm = this_base->pool().find_or_create(*this_base, details))\n    set_commodity(*ann_comm);\n}\n```\n\n### Flow:\n1. Extract base commodity (either directly or via annotated wrapper)\n2. Call `commodity_pool_t::find_or_create(base_commodity, annotation_t)`\n3. If it doesn't exist, create it via `commodity_pool_t::create()`\n4. Set the amount's commodity pointer to the annotated commodity\n\nThis is how `exchange()` attaches the annotation: it calls the `amount_t` constructor with annotation:\n```cpp\namount_t(const amount_t& amt, const annotation_t& details)  // line 209-214 of amount.h\n```\nwhich internally calls `annotate(details)`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Manual